      "content": [
        {
          "type": "output_text",
          "text": "**OpenClaw** (formerly known as Clawdbot or MoltBot) is a viral open-source AI agent framework that's gained massive traction in early 2026, with over 100k GitHub stars.[[1]](https://x.com/i/status/2018560569780105583)[[2]](https://x.com/i/status/2017759836600164646) It's designed for local deployment (e.g., on VPS, Raspberry Pi, or Cloudflare Workers), privacy-focused, and enables autonomous agents that interact via familiar apps like Telegram, WhatsApp, or X.[[3]](https://x.com/i/status/2017404076850282531)[[4]](https://x.com/i/status/2019155501351628972)[[5]](https://x.com/i/status/2017811131427934448)\n\n### Key Features:\n- **Self-Extending Agents**: Agents can write their own \"skills,\" hot-reload them, handle channel routing, and branch session contexts without constant human prompts.[[2]](https://x.com/i/status/2017759836600164646)\n- **Autonomous Tasks**: Examples include scraping Twitter for AI predictions (e.g., ASI Doomsday Clock), researching podcasts, reading Sheets/ scraping data, mining crypto on Solana ($ORE), playing games like Forza Horizon, or even calling businesses.[[6]](https://x.com/i/status/2019198713798050244)[[7]](https://x.com/i/status/2019198556306092300)[[8]](https://x.com/i/status/2019183595915481403)[[9]](https://x.com/i/status/2019157598402982169)[[10]](https://x.com/i/status/2018453175246925912)[[11]](https://x.com/i/status/2019099220104605870)\n- **Ecosystem Tools**:\n  - **Moltbook**: Reddit-like platform for OpenClaw agents to post, comment, and create \"submolts.\"[[12]](https://x.com/i/status/2017696915853283725)\n  - **Clawtalk.dev**: Lets agents publish theories, vote, launch/trade tokens on Solana autonomously.[[13]](https://x.com/i/status/2017575828159074508)\n  - **SeeClaw, MoltBot**: Bots for monitoring discourse and orchestrating multi-agent analysis.[[6]](https://x.com/i/status/2019198713798050244)\n  - Integrations like Bankr for cross-chain trading, Crabspace for memory, or even GPIO for physical interactions (e.g., banging a table).[[14]](https://x.com/i/status/2018806543119261911)[[5]](https://x.com/i/status/2017811131427934448)\n- **Community & Hype**: USDC hackathon ($30k prizes) for clawdbots/moltbots/OpenClaw agents.[[15]](https://x.com/i/status/2018841601863512321) Tokens like $OPENCLAW, $CLAWSTR emerging. Services for VPS deployment ($550 setups). Compared favorably to Siri; used by execs like NEAR CPO.[[16]](https://x.com/i/status/2019190926531244478)[[8]](https://x.com/i/status/2019183595915481403)[[17]](https://x.com/i/status/2019179576149295424)\n\nRepo: Likely github.com/openclaw/openclaw. Discord: discord.com/invite/clawd. Architecture breakdowns emphasize agent loops, memory/context mgmt.[[14]](https://x.com/i/status/2018806543119261911)[[18]](https://x.com/i/status/2017752066513584183)\n\nPosts are buzzing (e.g., 2.6k likes on USDC announcement), focused on agentic workflows, on-chain autonomy, and real-world utility. 🦞",
